CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper August 1, 1953, pg. 1, reads: "Young Artist Returns - Talented Olive Moorefield, Homestead's promising young concert singer, returned from Austria on a surprise visit home this week. She had been on a concert tour as a member of a goodwill show, sponsored by the United States State Department. The tour covered forty cities and towns and Miss Moorefield received enthusiastic response from press and audience throughout Austria. Following a six week stay, she will return to Austria to fulfil film and recording commitments. The Courier photographer snapped this picture as Olive alighted from the plane which brought her from New York Tuesday night. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Singer Olive Moorefield deplaning from Capital Airlines airplane
